+
+## Sub-round 6f — homebrew caster slots on the live sheet
+
+Homebrew class spellcasting now reaches the character sheet rather than stopping
+at packet normalization.
+
+- `src/lib/multiclass.ts` accepts an optional `RulesContentRegistry` when
+  calculating caster contributions and combined slots. Homebrew full, half,
+  third, and pact casters use their pinned class packet. A single-class
+  homebrew caster uses its authored native slot table. Custom tables remain
+  native-only because the payload has no explicit multiclass contribution rule.
+- `src/components/HeroSheet.tsx` builds the resolved class registry before sheet
+  calculations and uses `combinedSpellSlots` for slot maxima, preserving pact
+  slots as a separate pool.
+- `tests/multiclassFoundation.test.ts` covers native homebrew full-caster slots
+  plus combined full and half homebrew caster contributions.
+
+This closes the previously documented sheet-level homebrew caster-slot deferral.
